German Chancellor Merkel

02:53.406 --> 02:55.473
called the comment by
the American president:

02:55.476 --> 02:56.371
"Unhelpful..."

02:56.372 --> 02:58.051
I do the most

02:58.054 --> 03:00.234
least amount of bragging...

03:00.237 --> 03:02.465
word "house" instead of "hole."

03:02.468 --> 03:03.605
As in, "shit house..."

03:03.606 --> 03:05.438
tropical storm Don Jr.

03:05.439 --> 03:07.778
About to make landfall
in Cuba, and on the...

03:07.781 --> 03:10.438
new species of fungus
named covfefe originalis,

03:10.439 --> 03:11.812
after the president's...

03:11.815 --> 03:14.309
piece from the Ivanka Trump collection.

03:14.312 --> 03:16.481
And here's a really
nice piece from the...

03:16.484 --> 03:19.204
Now let's see how our
friends on the farm are doing.

03:19.205 --> 03:20.536
I'm tired.

03:20.539 --> 03:22.405
I can't sleep either.

03:22.406 --> 03:24.610
We'll have to count
little boys and girls.

03:24.613 --> 03:27.278
How can you sleep when
Donald Trump is president?

03:27.281 --> 03:28.971
Just look at North Korea.

03:28.972 --> 03:31.171
They've got their missiles
pointed right at us, and...

03:31.172 --> 03:33.933
Are you tired of being
tired? Sick of being sick?

03:37.726 --> 03:40.937
- Hello?
- Hey, invite me over right now.

03:40.938 --> 03:42.304
Tully?

03:42.305 --> 03:45.038
Yeah. Come on. Let's
have a glass of wine.

03:45.039 --> 03:46.904
Tully, I'm in bed.

03:46.905 --> 03:49.904
Ooh. What're you wearing?

03:49.905 --> 03:52.871
We said it was a one-night thing, Tully.

03:52.872 --> 03:55.153
Where are you? It sounds
like someone's being killed.

03:55.156 --> 03:57.359
I'm downtown.

03:57.362 --> 03:59.408
The police are overreacting.

03:59.411 --> 04:01.043
Hey, guys, keep it down.

04:01.046 --> 04:02.171
I'm on the phone.

04:02.172 --> 04:03.715
What are you protesting now?

04:03.718 --> 04:06.817
Come on down and find out.
It's, uh, very exciting.

04:06.820 --> 04:09.971
No. I think I'm in for the night.

04:09.972 --> 04:12.020
- Um, stay safe.
- Diane.

04:12.023 --> 04:15.778
Now wait. You know we-we had
something great going, right?

04:17.139 --> 04:20.978
That's my call-waiting. Good night.

04:20.982 --> 04:22.981
- Who is that, your other lover?
- Good night.

04:22.984 --> 04:24.403
Don't kill anyone.

04:24.406 --> 04:26.271
Hello?

04:26.272 --> 04:28.957
Still me. See, I think
subconsciously you wanted it

04:28.960 --> 04:30.325
to be me...

04:30.328 --> 04:31.904
- Hello?
- Diane.

04:31.905 --> 04:33.138
Sorry to call you at home.

04:33.139 --> 04:34.723
Oh, no, I'm awake.

04:34.726 --> 04:37.171
The network wants to broadcast
something on its morning show,

04:37.172 --> 04:38.937
and they're getting some pushback.

04:38.938 --> 04:40.238
We're outside counsel

04:40.239 --> 04:42.138
and we only have eight
hours to sort this out.

04:42.139 --> 04:44.171
Well, who's the pushback coming from?

04:44.172 --> 04:46.528
Old friend of yours.

04:49.500 --> 04:51.731
- Mr. Burl Preston.
- Yes, it's me.

04:51.734 --> 04:53.799
And I've forgotten your name.

04:53.800 --> 04:55.566
- Diane Lockhart.
- Diane.

04:55.567 --> 04:58.148
And this is my partner
in crime, Adrian Boseman.

04:58.151 --> 04:59.483
Mr. Preston.

04:59.486 --> 05:01.117
I heard your house burned down.

05:01.120 --> 05:03.553
I'm sorry. Dangers of canyon living.

05:03.556 --> 05:05.499
Don't cry for me, I have two more.

05:05.500 --> 05:08.899
And I heard clients are
killing lawyers in Chicago.

05:08.900 --> 05:10.466
Yes, one or two.

05:10.467 --> 05:11.733
Well, you're taking it well.

05:11.734 --> 05:13.772
Well, Chicago. We're used to worse.

05:13.775 --> 05:16.200
Uh, we're just in with our
clients right now, Mr. Preston.

05:16.203 --> 05:17.632
We'll be out to get
you in a few minutes.

05:17.633 --> 05:18.817
Sure, I'll just sit here.

05:18.820 --> 05:21.833
After four hours jetting
into a snowstorm, why not?

05:21.834 --> 05:23.382
I got all the time in the world.

05:23.385 --> 05:25.084
You're the ones who are in such a hurry

05:25.087 --> 05:26.201
to air this nonsense.

05:26.204 --> 05:28.536
It's not a black and
white situation, Greg.

05:28.539 --> 05:30.666
There are photos of the
woman arm-in-arm with him.

05:30.667 --> 05:31.933
- Is he here?
- Yeah.

05:31.934 --> 05:33.299
Is he mad?

05:33.300 --> 05:34.804
What?

05:34.807 --> 05:36.599
Is it gonna be a testy negotiation?

05:36.600 --> 05:39.343
I don't think it's going
to be a negotiation at all.

05:39.346 --> 05:41.309
This is a First Amendment issue.

05:41.312 --> 05:44.000
You have a news story. It's
yours to broadcast or not.

05:44.003 --> 05:45.109
Unless it's defamatory.

05:45.112 --> 05:46.631
- Well, there's no reason...
- Well, let's not get

05:46.633 --> 05:47.666
ahead of ourselves, okay?

05:48.800 --> 05:52.629
Okay, okay, okay, wait.
Carter is our in-house counsel.

05:52.632 --> 05:54.499
He keeps us from doing anything stupid.

05:54.500 --> 05:55.833
Reddick/Boseman,

05:55.834 --> 05:58.165
you defend us if we end
up doing anything stupid.

05:58.166 --> 06:00.833
So we all have a role here.

06:00.834 --> 06:02.566
And we have seven hours to figure out

06:02.567 --> 06:04.466
whether to broadcast this story.

06:04.467 --> 06:06.267
So let's start.

06:19.633 --> 06:20.899
So what's this about?

06:20.900 --> 06:24.046
You stay with us, and
give us a report card?

06:24.049 --> 06:26.532
Yeah. And offer suggestions on the law

06:26.533 --> 06:28.799
and how it can be obeyed.

06:28.800 --> 06:30.833
And, what, we get, like,
a grade on our windshield?

06:30.834 --> 06:32.733
- Like those restaurants?
- And everybody avoids

06:32.734 --> 06:34.859
getting arrested by a car with a "C."

06:36.467 --> 06:38.532
So you do this every night?

06:38.533 --> 06:41.199
No, once a month.

06:41.200 --> 06:44.382
And other lawyers from other
firms follow other cops.

06:44.385 --> 06:46.918
Aren't you guys dodging
bullets these days?

06:46.921 --> 06:48.653
That's right. People hate you lawyers.

06:48.656 --> 06:49.968
I thought we were hated.

06:49.971 --> 06:52.604
It's overblown. It
was just a few lawyers.

06:52.607 --> 06:54.835
What about that lawyer that
hanged himself yesterday?

06:54.838 --> 06:56.570
You know, people aren't
thinking he did it,

06:56.573 --> 06:57.739
it was done to him.

06:57.742 --> 06:59.632
Who was that?

06:59.633 --> 07:01.699
I don't know his name.

07:01.700 --> 07:03.173
It was over in Highland Park,

07:03.176 --> 07:04.914
- I think.
- Hey.

07:04.917 --> 07:07.082
Here comes the big action for the night.

07:07.085 --> 07:08.789
Get ready.

07:18.330 --> 07:19.663
There it is!

07:19.664 --> 07:22.930
- Every single night.
- Readjusting the package.

07:28.101 --> 07:33.075
_

07:33.078 --> 07:34.928
RMP Eleven-Thirty-Nine.

07:34.931 --> 07:36.530
Code Three pursuit of a white,

07:36.531 --> 07:38.663
late-model Camaro, Tennessee tags,

07:38.664 --> 07:41.075
"Three, Six, Tom, Victor, David."

07:43.064 --> 07:44.463
vicinity of Code Five.

08:11.633 --> 08:12.664
Aah.

08:54.026 --> 08:56.058
The list of prominent men accused

08:56.061 --> 08:57.760
of sexual harassment continues to grow

08:57.763 --> 08:59.820
even six months after Harvey Weinstein.

08:59.823 --> 09:01.166
Now the biggest

09:01.169 --> 09:02.895
and potentially most explosive name

09:02.898 --> 09:05.363
has been added to the
list. Kip Dunning...

09:05.364 --> 09:07.985
- Pause here.
- "Please."

09:07.988 --> 09:09.856
Please.

09:09.859 --> 09:11.934
We obviously object to the story

09:11.937 --> 09:13.496
top to bottom, and will immediately

09:13.497 --> 09:15.796
sue for damages, but I want to point out

09:15.797 --> 09:19.396
how sloppy this story is. "Alleged."

09:19.397 --> 09:20.730
Where is the word "alleged"?

09:20.731 --> 09:22.181
- So you'd like that added to the copy?
- No.

09:22.183 --> 09:23.438
As I already stated,

09:23.441 --> 09:25.895
this whole story is
defamatory and should be cut.

09:25.898 --> 09:27.730
So can we move on, please?

09:27.738 --> 09:29.771
Certainly. Play.

09:32.131 --> 09:33.763
Please.

09:33.766 --> 09:35.496
Kip Dunning

09:35.497 --> 09:37.630
is an actor with a
reputation rarely matched

09:37.631 --> 09:39.789
- in the Hollywood firmament...
- Oh, come on.

09:39.792 --> 09:43.469
Talk about cynical. You use
a still... Pause, please.

09:43.472 --> 09:45.618
And notice "please."

09:45.621 --> 09:47.287
You use a still

09:47.290 --> 09:50.552
from an action movie to suggest
Kip is aggressive to women.

09:50.555 --> 09:51.891
This is the nicest actor

09:51.894 --> 09:52.926
on the face of the earth,

09:52.929 --> 09:54.669
and you place him in
a defamatory light...

09:54.672 --> 09:56.763
You want us to change
out the photo? Great.

09:56.764 --> 09:58.765
- I'm sure we can do that.
- My individual issues

09:58.768 --> 10:00.883
in no way undercut the main point:

10:00.886 --> 10:03.665
this report is defamatory.

10:03.668 --> 10:07.141
Please, if you'd be so kind, play.

10:09.117 --> 10:12.584
And now two women have come
forward to accuse Dunning

10:12.587 --> 10:15.730
of both sexual assault and rape.

10:15.731 --> 10:17.763
He told me I'd have a career.

10:17.766 --> 10:19.365
He said everybody did it.

10:19.368 --> 10:20.877
- This was my idol...
- Okay, here it is.

10:20.879 --> 10:21.912
Stop, please.

10:21.915 --> 10:23.963
You use an anonymous woman,

10:23.964 --> 10:25.668
someone Kip can't confront,

10:25.671 --> 10:27.930
to charge him with forced oral rape.

10:27.931 --> 10:31.262
That, to put it simply, is bullshit.

10:31.265 --> 10:32.696
The reporter did a thorough check...

10:32.697 --> 10:35.598
We all know that these
days, even the whisper

10:35.601 --> 10:37.348
of a sexual harassment charge

10:37.351 --> 10:39.597
ruins a career for life.

10:39.600 --> 10:41.571
Yes, and that's why this story was sent

10:41.574 --> 10:43.257
to Kip, so he or his representatives

10:43.260 --> 10:44.259
could comment on it.

10:44.262 --> 10:46.097
We're willing to put
his comment in the story.

10:46.098 --> 10:47.496
And we're willing to
address your objections

10:47.497 --> 10:48.863
by re-editing the story.

10:53.919 --> 10:57.173
My objection is you're being used.

10:57.176 --> 10:59.429
Sexual harassment is
no longer the province

10:59.430 --> 11:02.316
of "MeToo" hashtags. It's
being used politically.

11:02.319 --> 11:05.009
And Kip has made so many
enemies among the alt-right,

11:05.012 --> 11:07.963
this is a hack job from them.

11:07.964 --> 11:09.663
We've invited the reporter in

11:09.664 --> 11:12.063
to defend her report, so please
stick around, Mr. Preston.

11:12.064 --> 11:15.032
Sure. I'm still on L.A. time.

11:15.035 --> 11:17.354
It's only 9:00 p.m. to me.

11:17.357 --> 11:20.189
Thank you.

11:20.192 --> 11:22.192
You're welcome.

11:30.129 --> 11:32.097
Mr. Bloom.

11:32.098 --> 11:33.630
Don't do that.

11:33.631 --> 11:35.410
Do what?

11:35.413 --> 11:37.630
Show him that we're not a united front.

11:37.631 --> 11:39.782
Give him any hope
whatsoever that we will cave.

11:39.785 --> 11:40.763
I didn't do that.

11:40.764 --> 11:42.363
- That is bullshit.
- I didn't do that.

11:42.364 --> 11:43.363
Yes, you did.

11:44.937 --> 11:46.767
You're insulting my
intelligence right now...

11:46.770 --> 11:47.930
Wait, wait.

11:47.931 --> 11:51.063
I want in-house counsel
and out-house counsel.

11:51.064 --> 11:53.576
Excuse me, outside counsel,

11:53.579 --> 11:54.978
to work together.

11:54.981 --> 11:57.587
So let's discuss what
we'll say before we say it.

11:57.590 --> 11:59.363
Agreed.

11:59.364 --> 12:02.824
Uh, uh, Diane. Marissa, come.

12:09.397 --> 12:12.329
Diane.

12:12.330 --> 12:14.663
I don't trust their in-house counsel.

12:14.664 --> 12:17.212
Well, he gets paid
if there are no suits.

12:17.215 --> 12:18.821
We get paid if we win suits.

12:18.824 --> 12:19.926
Makes him cowardly.

12:19.929 --> 12:21.241
Well, what do you want from us?

12:21.244 --> 12:22.326
We only have a few more hours,

12:22.328 --> 12:24.301
so I need you to look
into the two accusers.

12:24.304 --> 12:26.041
Marissa, you take the anonymous accuser.

12:26.044 --> 12:27.110
Jay, you take the other.

12:27.113 --> 12:28.791
They're not gonna be
happy about being woken up.

12:28.793 --> 12:30.657
My guess is that these stories stand up,

12:30.660 --> 12:32.923
but Preston makes a good
point about the alt-right.

12:32.926 --> 12:35.429
Find out if this is a setup.

12:35.430 --> 12:37.658
Don't believe the women? It's not that.

12:37.661 --> 12:40.694
We're in the second wave of
these harassment charges, Diane.

12:40.695 --> 12:43.760
Certain people are using
it for political advantage.

12:43.761 --> 12:45.259
Let's just be sure

12:45.262 --> 12:48.860
our charges stand up. All right?

12:48.861 --> 12:51.794
- Okay, we're on it.
- Good.

12:51.795 --> 12:55.061
Should I call Lucca?

12:55.062 --> 12:57.902
No. She and Maia are
on consent decree duty.

12:57.905 --> 12:59.195
Oh, oh, right.

13:01.128 --> 13:03.626
Hey, did you see another
lawyer got killed?

13:03.629 --> 13:06.407
- What? Who?
- Wilk Hobson.

13:06.410 --> 13:08.376
Oh.

13:08.379 --> 13:10.199
- You know him?
- Yes.

13:10.202 --> 13:12.375
He and my late partner, Will Gardner,

13:12.378 --> 13:14.694
once got in a fistfight. My God.

13:14.695 --> 13:16.194
What happened?

13:16.195 --> 13:18.863
He was found hanged
in his vacation home.

13:18.866 --> 13:21.231
He was found hanged? So...

13:21.234 --> 13:22.727
Wait, was he killed, or...

13:22.728 --> 13:24.094
Police don't know.

13:24.095 --> 13:26.261
He had sued somebody
on a slip-and-fall,

13:26.262 --> 13:28.527
and the other client had threatened him.

13:28.528 --> 13:31.161
Wow.

13:31.162 --> 13:34.940
The year of living dangerously.

13:47.860 --> 13:50.259
How long do these
pursuits usually go on for?

13:50.262 --> 13:51.794
We can let you out.

13:51.795 --> 13:54.418
No, no, I... I was just wondering.

14:04.494 --> 14:05.926
Put your fucking hands up!

14:05.929 --> 14:07.681
Don't move, motherfucker, don't move!

14:07.684 --> 14:08.794
Stay here.

14:08.795 --> 14:10.794
