We're running it.

47:37.183 --> 47:39.382
And you wonder why people
are killing lawyers.

47:39.385 --> 47:40.593
Here.

47:40.596 --> 47:41.962
There you go.

47:44.385 --> 47:45.751
What's this?

47:45.752 --> 47:47.928
It's our lawsuit. See you in court.

47:55.352 --> 47:57.518
Yeah.

47:57.519 --> 47:59.460
We'll see him in court.

48:03.139 --> 48:06.350
_

48:09.297 --> 48:10.730
Well, you're pretty quiet.

48:10.733 --> 48:12.351
You all right?

48:12.352 --> 48:14.022
Fine.

48:14.025 --> 48:15.957
Put your clothes in the wash right away

48:15.960 --> 48:19.201
or the smell stays forever.

48:19.204 --> 48:20.538
Good luck.

48:47.319 --> 48:49.796
Officer Torino, do you have a second?

48:53.481 --> 48:55.480
Yeah?

48:55.483 --> 48:59.808
Uh, I don't want to
put this on my report,

48:59.811 --> 49:02.751
so if you just put the stuff you stole

49:02.752 --> 49:05.518
into evidence, I won't say anything.

49:05.519 --> 49:07.218
What are you talking about?

49:11.816 --> 49:13.316
Put the stuff into evidence

49:13.319 --> 49:15.218
and I will erase this.

49:22.497 --> 49:24.288
This is Tommy and this is Crystal.

49:24.291 --> 49:25.590
Who's Tommy?

49:25.593 --> 49:27.186
The dead man in the apartment.

49:27.189 --> 49:28.647
He's a retired cop.

49:28.650 --> 49:30.115
You knew him?

49:30.118 --> 49:32.117
No. He was in another district.

49:32.120 --> 49:34.113
So why did you take his things?

49:34.116 --> 49:37.549
This is Crystal.

49:37.552 --> 49:39.351
His wife's name is Patricia.

49:39.352 --> 49:40.694
They were separated,

49:40.697 --> 49:43.562
but that apartment was
where he met his girlfriend.

49:43.565 --> 49:45.231
Now, cops have a rule:

49:45.234 --> 49:48.022
don't let any guy's
wife find out anything

49:48.025 --> 49:49.824
you wouldn't want your
own wife finding out,

49:49.827 --> 49:51.215
so I took the picture

49:51.218 --> 49:52.928
of Tommy and his girlfriend

49:52.931 --> 49:55.983
'cause I didn't want it to be
Patricia's last memory of him.

49:55.986 --> 49:58.115
And I took the jewelry
that he was giving Crystal

49:58.118 --> 50:00.318
so that I could send it to his wife,

50:00.319 --> 50:03.118
saying it was his last
wish that she get it.

50:05.400 --> 50:08.599
Is there anything else, Maia?

50:08.602 --> 50:10.035
No.

50:10.038 --> 50:13.652
I hope you enjoyed the ride-along.

50:18.627 --> 50:22.004
Hi. There is a protester here

50:22.007 --> 50:24.318
who wasn't allowed to sign an I-bond

50:24.319 --> 50:27.217
- and he needs $200.
- Name?

50:27.218 --> 50:29.885
Tully.

50:29.886 --> 50:32.482
I actually don't know his last name.

50:32.485 --> 50:36.624
Um, can I just leave,
uh, bail for him and go?

50:36.627 --> 50:38.584
I-I guess he's the leader.

50:38.585 --> 50:40.761
Sure, I know him. Talks a lot?

50:40.764 --> 50:42.007
That's right.

50:42.010 --> 50:44.749
Uh, can I just, you know, leave it here?

50:44.752 --> 50:46.384
Want a receipt?

50:46.385 --> 50:47.885
No. That's okay.

50:59.077 --> 51:01.851
You all right, Captain Quinn?

51:01.852 --> 51:04.651
Just a bit of car
sickness, Officer Rindell.

51:04.652 --> 51:06.491
- Ouch.
- I know.

51:06.494 --> 51:08.020
Car sickness?

51:08.023 --> 51:09.988
Yours must've been intense.

51:09.991 --> 51:11.957
Yeah, it, it had moments.

51:11.960 --> 51:13.326
Yours?

51:13.329 --> 51:15.061
Same.

51:22.686 --> 51:24.251
You want to grab some breakfast?

51:24.252 --> 51:25.484
Uh, yeah.

51:25.485 --> 51:27.484
Yeah, that'd be really...

51:27.485 --> 51:30.552
You may have something
else to tend to first.

51:32.886 --> 51:34.171
See you tomorrow?

51:34.174 --> 51:36.468
Yeah. Go home and get some sleep.

51:51.884 --> 51:54.050
Did you make sure Francesca drank water?

51:54.053 --> 51:56.358
I did, I did.

51:56.361 --> 51:58.816
She, uh, will have dry mouth for a week.

51:58.819 --> 52:00.384
But...

52:00.385 --> 52:03.284
- listen, about what you said earlier...
- Colin.

52:03.285 --> 52:06.699
Seriously... I just supplied
you with information, that...

52:06.702 --> 52:07.751
Marry me.

52:15.752 --> 52:19.551
I'm walking away.

52:19.552 --> 52:22.284
This is your car.

52:22.285 --> 52:24.484
That's right.

52:24.485 --> 52:26.384
I'm driving away.

52:26.385 --> 52:28.818
It's not a dumb idea.

52:28.819 --> 52:32.284
Colin Morrello...

52:32.285 --> 52:34.386
no fucking way.

52:34.389 --> 52:36.284
- Why not?
- Three hours ago,

52:36.285 --> 52:37.663
you were fucking another woman.

52:37.666 --> 52:39.147
Yeah, well, I'm a tad more informed

52:39.150 --> 52:40.483
than I was three hours ago.

52:40.486 --> 52:42.685
- That doesn't change shit.
- It changes everything.

52:42.688 --> 52:45.527
Pregnancy is not a good
enough reason to get married.

52:45.530 --> 52:49.217
Yeah, well, it's a start.

52:51.852 --> 52:54.475
Seriously? Colin.

52:59.652 --> 53:01.397
No.

